BFN 

  [Text] Paris, May 4 KYODO -- Japanese Prime Minister 
Tsutomu Hata arrived in Paris shortly before noon Wednesday [4 
May] from Rome for talks with French leaders on bilateral and 
international relations and the July 8-10 Naples economic summit. 
  Hata is scheduled to meet with French President Francois 
Mitterrand, Prime Minister Edouard Balladur and Paris Mayor 
Jacques Chirac before flying to Germany on Thursday. 
  Hata will also visit Belgium before returning to Tokyo. 

